    <item>
      <title>On Beauty and Mathematics</title>
      <link>https://rud72k.github.io/post.html?id=on-beauty-and-mathematics</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://rud72k.github.io/post.html?id=on-beauty-and-mathematics</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[
        There is a peculiar kind of joy in discovering that something deeply abstract — a proof, a formula — possesses the same qualities we assign to a sunset or a piece of music.
      ]]></description>
      <category>math</category>
      <category>essay</category>
    </item>

    <item>
      <title>The Weight of Words</title>
      <link>https://rud72k.github.io/post.html?id=the-weight-of-words</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://rud72k.github.io/post.html?id=the-weight-of-words</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[
        Language is not a neutral vessel. Every word carries sediment — centuries of use, misuse, and repurposing. When we write, we inherit all of it.
      ]]></description>
      <category>language</category>
      <category>craft</category>
